    <p>In this video we will discuss about</p><p>Why become an entrepreneur to be successfull and Unsuccessful Entrepreneurs</p><p>The characteristics listed describe a demographic profile often associated with entrepreneurs, particularly in the context of small to medium-sized businesses. However, it's essential to note that entrepreneurship isn't limited to individuals fitting these criteria. </p><p>1. **Firstborns**: While being a firstborn may confer certain personality traits such as leadership qualities and responsibility, it's not a strict determinant of entrepreneurial success. Entrepreneurs can come from any birth order.</p><p>2. **Age Range 30-50**: This age range often represents a stage in life where individuals have gained sufficient experience and knowledge in their respective fields. They may also have accumulated financial resources and established professional networks, which can be advantageous for starting a business.
